What installer are you using?
By default, the Epp client requires internet access to install if the dependencies are missing.
You can try to install the dependencies shown in the list before installing the Epp client.
Or you can request a FAT client.

Kind regards
__________________
Andrei Pop | Technical Support Engineer
Netwrix Endpoint Protector

TextBody:
Hello,

Thank you for the update.
During install did it show any errors?
Can the Epp client icon be seen on the computer?
Please open the Epp client go to the settings tab and press ctrl + alt + i to see if an IP is set.

Can you please also collect a set of logs using the commands below on the terminal?
cd /var/log/epp-client/
touch /var/log/epp-client/epp_client_daemon.log
touch /var/log/epp-client/eppsslsplit.log
sudo service epp-client-daemon restart

Kind regards
__________________
Andrei Pop | Technical Support Engineer
Netwrix Endpoint Protector
